re skating's team event, and the U.S., which won silver, will become the Olympic champions.\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 244, \"end\": 250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9994887561986552, \"rank\": 0.0004213635993550382, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The decision\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 237}, {\"ngram\": \"its gold medal\", \"from\": 271, \"to\": 285}, {\"ngram\": \"figure skating's team event\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 316}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 330}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 348}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic champions\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee did not present any medals in Beijing for the event after Valieva's test results turned up positive for a banned heart medicine hours after she helped Russia win gold.\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 389, \"end\": 420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 451, \"end\": 458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9990256595795302, \"rank\": 0.0009752906853115375, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 572, \"end\": 578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9994887561986552, \"rank\": 0.0004213635993550382, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any medals\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 447}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 472}, {\"ngram\": \"Valieva's test results\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"a banned heart medicine\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 587}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement Japan won bronze and Canada placed fourth in the team event.\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 605, \"end\": 610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.8477641992561491, \"rank\": 0.11669943678306259, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.8739780383644926, \"rank\": 0.13807553341232393, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 620}, {\"ngram\": \"the team event\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 663}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee said at the time that it would \\\"organize dignified medal ceremonies once the case of Ms. Valieva has been concluded.\\\"\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 670, \"end\": 701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \